OrthoPrax庐 is the most comprehensive Christian Orthodox Calendar and lectionary available for iOS, allowing you to experience the Liturgical cycle of the Ancient Faith according to the calendar.  Carry all the prayers, fasting schedules, daily Scripture readings, biographies of the daily saints and more to read wherever you are, following the Old Calendar or the Old Calendar!  Developed in the Serbian tradition, it will soon support Greek, Antiochian, Russian and OCA saints, feast days, with specifics and added themes for the various jurisdictions.

Content includes:

鈥 Most comprehensive collection of Saints for each day;
鈥 Most comprehensive collection of curated icons (3,500+) for the Saints and Feast days;
鈥 Fasting guidelines;
鈥 Readings;
鈥 Daily prayers.

An UPDATED compendium and ONLY iOS version of The Prologue of Ohrid (鈥淧rologue鈥) is provided in collaboration with St. Sebastian Orthodox Press (鈥淪ebastian Press鈥), the book publishing ministry of the Serbian Orthodox Diocese of Western America.  First written by Saint Nikolai Velimirovic, who reposed in 1956, your subscription to Prologue, includes the thousands of Saints added in the most recent 2017 release, and is updated on a monthly basis.

An annual subscription to our Basic Calendar application is offered, and through an in-app purchase full text and audio content.

Subscription & Pricing Terms

OrthoPrax庐 is the ultimate Christian Orthodox calendar, prayer book, and guide with 3,500+ curated icons, daily prayers, and readings to help you experience and enjoy the liturgical cycle of the Ancient Faith. In-app purchases provide access to rich textual and audio content such as Sebastian Press鈥 Prologue, where our content would require hundreds of dollars to purchase separately, and a Cathedral in which to share our icons!

Free version: Contains the calendar, a listing of all Saints for every day, daily readings, daily prayers, the hymn of the day according to St. Nikolai Velimirovic, and thoughts of the day. When viewing the calendar, users see fasting and non-fasting days, can change from old calendar to new, and all icons are included as thumbnail images. The calendar is periodically updated to adjust for moving feast days, additional icons, and relevant changes to the readings.

Basic version ($3.99 per year): Adds the ability to access one icon (per Saint and Feast day where available) in high quality images, and to read summaries of the lives of the Saints from Sebastian Press鈥 Prologue (ISBN 9780971950504), as updated on a monthly basis.  

Full version ($14.99 per year): Adds the full text of Sebastian Press鈥 Prologue, providing on a daily basis, the Lives of the Saints, Hymns of Praise, Reflection, Contemplation and Homily for each day 鈥 a $135 value. In addition, you will have access to our complete icon database (multiple icons per Saint and Feast day where available) in high quality images, and the daily readings from Prologue brought alive with Fr. Norman Kosanovic鈥檚 broadcast voice!

Basic terms of purchase:

Refunds are not provided for unused portions of any subscription term, you will have access until the end of the current payment period. Subscriptions renew as of the date first enrolled, and users must retain their Basic version subscription in order to have access to the add-on subscriptions of the Full version, and:

鈥 Payments will be charged to your iTunes Account at confirmation of purchase;
鈥 Subscription automatically renews unless auto-renew is turned off at least 24-hours before the end of the current period;
鈥 Account will be charged for renewal within 24-hours prior to the end of the current period, and identify the cost of the renewal;
鈥 Subscriptions may be managed by the user and auto-renewal may be turned off by going to the user's Account Settings after purchase;
鈥 Unused portions of a free trial period, if offered, will be forfeited when the user purchases a subscription to that publication, where applicable.

